      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix and knead the dough",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine the {{strong-bread-flour}}, {{yeast-fast-action}}, {{sea-salt-fine}}, and the {{caster-sugar}} for the dough in a large bowl. Beat the {{eggs}} for the dough and mix with the {{whole-milk}} for the dough. Pour into the flour and mix to a rough dough. Knead for 5 minutes, then add the {{unsalted-butter}} for the dough in four pieces, working each in before adding the next. Knead for a further 5 minutes until the dough is smooth and slightly tacky. It will be softer than a lean dough.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "First rise, 90 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cover and leave in a warm place for 90 minutes until roughly doubled.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the filling",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the {{unsalted-butter}} for the filling with the {{caster-sugar}} and the {{cardamom-green}}. Keep beating until you have a smooth, spreadable paste.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shape the knots",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Roll the dough out on a lightly floured surface to a rectangle about 40 × 30 cm. Spread the cardamom filling evenly over the lower half. Fold the bare top half down over the filling to make a 40 × 15 cm rectangle. Press firmly to seal the layers. Cut into 12 strips (each about 3 cm wide). To shape each ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "cardamom knot",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp9yfhsk0000r4v424p7781w"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ": hold one end of the strip and wind the strip loosely around two fingers twice, then push the tail through the loop from below and tuck it under. Place on lined baking trays, leaving 4 cm between each.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Second rise, 30 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cover loosely and leave for 30 minutes until slightly puffed. Preheat the oven to 200°C fan.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Glaze and bake, 12 to 14 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Brush the buns with the beaten {{eggs}} glaze egg, then scatter the {{granulated-sugar}} over the top. Bake for 12 to 14 minutes until the buns are deep amber and the filling is bubbling at the edges. The base should feel firm when you lift one. Transfer to a rack and eat warm.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
